	December 31, 2011 to 38.6% for the year ended December 31, 2012, primarily due to the OPI acquisition and the Trumbull acquisition in 2011, partially offset by the depreciation of the Indian rupee against the U.S. dollar during the year
	ended December 31, 2012 compared to the year ended December 31, 2011.






