	Income from Operations.


	Income from operations increased 38.5% from $41.3 million
	for the year ended December 31, 2011 to $57.2 million for the year ended December 31, 2012. As a percentage of revenues, income from operations increased from 11.5% for the year ended December 31, 2011 to 12.9% for the year ended
	December 31, 2012. The increase in income from operations as a percentage of revenues was primarily due to our operating leverage, resulting in lower SG&A and depreciation and amortization expenses as a percentage of revenue in 2012.






