	The Companys provision for income taxes also includes the impact of provisions
	established for uncertain income tax positions determined in accordance with ASC No. 740,

	Income Taxes,

	as well as the related net interest. Tax exposures can involve complex issues and may require an extended resolution
	period. Although the Company believes that it has adequately reserved for its uncertain tax positions, no assurance can be given that the final tax outcome of these matters will not be different. The Company adjusts these reserves in light of
	changing facts and circumstances, such as the closing of a tax audit or the refinement of an estimate. To the extent that the final tax outcome of these matters differs from the amounts recorded, such differences will impact the provision for income
	taxes in the period in which such determination is made.


